            "summary": "RTX Corp. (NYSE: RTX) shares surged after its Collins Aerospace and Pratt & Whitney units announced significant deals. Pratt & Whitney has partnered with MTU Aero Engines to enhance GTF overhaul capacity at MTU's facilities, increasing annual capacity to 600 shop visits across all GTF models. This positions MTU as one of the top service providers in Pratt & Whitney's GTF MRO network. Additionally, Pratt & Whitney and Delta Air Lines (NYSE: DAL) revealed an agreement to boost GTF overhaul capacity at Delta TechOps in Atlanta. More details can be found on Benzinga.com.",
